The Managing Director of Development Bank of Nigeria, Mr. Tony Okpanachi has been conferred with the fellowship of the Chartered Institute of Bankers of Nigeria (CIBN). The award was the first ever extraordinary Investiture of the Institute held outside the regular CIBN investiture series, a statement from the bank said. Okpanachi was given this honorary fellowship awards alongside other five distinguished bankers in recognition of their contributions to the Banking Industry and the nationâ€™s economy. He is a seasoned banker of over 29 years experience, the statement added. Okpanachi was appointed the pioneer Managing Director/CEO of Development Bank of Nigeria Plc (DBN) in January 2017. Before his appointment, he was the deputy managing director of Ecobank Nigeria. Prior to that, he was the managing director, Ecobank Kenya and Cluster Managing Director for East Africa (comprising Kenya, Uganda, Tanzania, Burundi, Rwanda, South Sudan and Ethiopia).  He was also at various times managing director of Ecobank Malawi and Regional Coordinator for Lagos and South West of Ecobank Nigeria.